	('/en/2018/08/23/watch-and-catch-pokemon-in-our-biggest-marathon-yet-bb715b2f8747/','Aug 23, 2018 - By Brian. Watch and catch Pok√©mon in our biggest marathon yet. Pok√©mon Day calls for another Twitch Pok√©mon Marathon. On February 27 at 10AM PT, we‚Äôre kicking off the next Pok√©mon Marathon on /TwitchPresents. With 10 TV seasons and 11 movies, this is the perfect chance to celebrate Pok√©mon with chat, watch episodes from Pok√©mon the Series: Diamond and Pearl, Pok√©mon the Series: Black & White, and Pok√©mon the Series: XY, and collect more badges with the Twitch Presents: Pok√©mon Badge Collector Extension. The marathon runs Thursdays through Sundays in English, French, German, Spanish, Italian, and Brazilian Portuguese. Mark your calendars, Trainers. We‚Äôll see you in chat. In the first episode of the Pok√©mon the Series, Ash Ketchum from Pallet Town is finally old enough to receive his first Pok√©mon from Professor Oak, but on the morning Ash is supposed to claim it, he oversleeps! By the time he arrives at Professor Oak‚Äôs, the three Pok√©mon he wanted have already been chosen by the other Trainers-in-training, including his rival, Gary! The only Pok√©mon remaining is a strong-willed Pikachu. Together, Ash and Pikachu embark on many exciting adventures. And now, we‚Äôre reliving those adventures on Twitch. If you think you have what it takes to become the ultimate Pok√©mon Trainer, prove it with the Twitch Presents: Pok√©mon Badge Collector extension. When Pok√©mon badges appear on-stream, collect them to earn points and compete with other viewers. Stay vigilant and you may even collect a rare Pok√©mon badge or two‚Ä¶ Follow /TwitchPresents for all the latest updates.',258,'Watch and catch Pok√©mon in our biggest marathon yet','

