	('/en/2016/10/31/were-on-the-way-to-pax-aus-836dce95fd87/','Oct 31, 2016 - By Evan Freitas. We‚Äôre on the way to PAX Aus. Once again Twitch is heading down under, for what some have described as ‚Äúdefinitely the furthest south‚Äù event of the year, and also one of the most fun. We can‚Äôt wait for you to come and say ‚ÄúG‚Äôday‚Äù on the PAX Aus floor while checking out the massive amount of content coming live from the show. Make sure you bookmark the PAX Aus 2016 Event portal, where you‚Äôll be able to find all the channels covering The Main, Wombat and GameSpot theatres, all the competitive gameplay at the PAX Arena, plus a host of local streamers streaming directly from the official Twitch booth. Full schedules are now posted for the channels, so prepare yourself accordingly. Meet & Greets. If you‚Äôre heading to PAX Aus, make sure you stop by our booth (#1100) where we‚Äôve organized meet & greets with a whole lot of Aussie streamers. It goes a bit like this‚Ä¶take a pic in our photo booth together, get it signed,, have a chat, grab A Twitch drawstring backpack, then make all your friends who didn‚Äôt go to PAX jealous. Check out who‚Äôs coming: Intel Streamer Zone. Think Australia is too far to travel for Intel? Think again. Intel is once again supporting Twitch streamers with state of the art gaming rigs right at the Twitch Booth, so you won‚Äôt have to miss them while they‚Äôre away. Feast your eyes on the schedule right here: PAX Aus Party. Want to come celebrate gaming, by partying with other gamers? The official PAX Aus Twitch party, being held at Bobby Mcgee‚Äôs, is your chance. You‚Äôll need to show us your Pax badge for entry and be advised it‚Äôs first come first serve, so get there early to avoid disappointment. See you in Melbourne!',305,'We‚Äôre on the way to PAX Aus','

https://cdn.m7g.twitch.tv/eae64763cab2144a06b0/assets/uploads/b7dd531eaa461e1e54d3cfd8526416b9.png?w=1200&amp;h=630&amp;fm=jpg&amp;auto=format
